                <head>210. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>On January 15, the Department of State issued a press release stating United
                    States views on and support for the proposed European Common Market and Free
                    Trade Area. For text of the statement, see Department of State <hi rend="italic"
                        >Bulletin</hi>, February 4, 1957, page 182. In telegram 1910 to Bonn,
                    January 11, also sent to the Embassies in the other five ECSC countries as well
                    as the United Kingdom, the Department transmitted an advance text of the
                    statement, and authorized the addressees to inform the respective Foreign
                    Offices informally <pb facs="0531" n="503" xml:id="pg_503"/> of the timing of
                    the announcement and to make the text available. (Department of State, Central
                    Files, 840.05/1–1157)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
